1
00:01:25,270 --> 00:01:32,000
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:35,000
[Episode 12]

3
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:25,190
♪ The wind blows over the hills ♪

4
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:32,270
♪ Carrying the scent of rice flowers ♪

5
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:39,520
♪ Moonlight dances on the river ♪

6
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:46,720
♪ Baby sleeps in peace ♪

7
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:21,160
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

8
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:24,630
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

9
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,760
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

10
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:32,750
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

11
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:37,570
♪ Wrath sets on end my hair,
I lean on railings ♪

12
00:03:38,579 --> 00:03:41,250
♪ Where I see
the drizzling rain has ceased ♪

13
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:45,210
♪ Raising my eyes ♪

14
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,120
♪ Towards the skies ♪

15
00:03:51,050 --> 00:03:53,060
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

16
00:03:54,790 --> 00:04:01,310
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

17
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:09,030
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

18
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:30,270
Wanfu.

19
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:31,640
Feel like eating meat?

20
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:06,060
Smells so good.

21
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,340
As good as it was back then.

22
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,670
Watching the steam rising from the steamers,

23
00:05:10,670 --> 00:05:11,640
I feel we have

24
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:13,070
the best days in our life.

25
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:17,310
It makes me feel at peace.

26
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:18,150
Take it.

27
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:18,920
Here.

28
00:05:18,970 --> 00:05:20,300
Waiter, get the dishes!

29
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,460
Coming!

30
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,770
Get the dishes.

31
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,020
We're in war time.

32
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:32,770
How come the restaurants in the concession
are doing so well?

33
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,380
These days

34
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,770
are really strange.

35
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:37,250
Every day on the street,

36
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:39,330
you see people freezing and starving to death,

37
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:40,390
yet many are making

38
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:42,310
more money than ever.

39
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:45,230
Especially the landlords and restaurant owners.

40
00:05:45,230 --> 00:05:46,090
Think about it.

41
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,900
Over a million people have come,

42
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:50,300
bringing all their savings and valuables.

43
00:05:50,470 --> 00:05:51,340
They need to have three meals a day,

44
00:05:51,340 --> 00:05:52,650
but they have nowhere to cook.

45
00:05:52,650 --> 00:05:54,560
Doesn't that benefit our restaurant?

46
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,810
Benefit who?

47
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,750
Boss.

48
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:01,240
They're ready.

49
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,530
Here, have a taste.

50
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,790
Great job!

51
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:13,550
It's the Shandong flavor.

52
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:16,120
Authentic Shandong flavor.

53
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,890
When Erbao recommended you to me,

54
00:06:18,890 --> 00:06:21,060
I thought he exaggerated your cooking skills.

55
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:23,110
Just settle down here and work for me.

56
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:24,040
Thank you, Boss.

57
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,310
Erbao.

58
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,240
The kitchen helper, Jin, left.

59
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,660
There's a spare bed now.

60
00:06:28,770 --> 00:06:30,230
When we close tonight,

61
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:31,230
take him with you

62
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:33,030
and let him sleep in that bed.

63
00:06:33,030 --> 00:06:33,760
Okay.

64
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,280
Thank you, Boss.

65
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:39,830
Our Shandong-flavored buns are ready!

66
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:45,700
Okay.

67
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:48,590
Buns are ready!

68
00:06:49,070 --> 00:06:50,070
Coming.

69
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,170
Here.

70
00:07:07,810 --> 00:07:13,270
[Juren Lane]

71
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,730
[Barber Shop]

72
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,820
[Juren Lane]

73
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:39,040
My eyebrows are short and thick.

74
00:07:40,390 --> 00:07:49,740
I'll just imagine I was born with phoenix eyes like Guan Yu.

75
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,170
Sister-in-law.

76
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:58,780
Did it burn you?

77
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,090
It's fine.

78
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:00,920
It's fine.

79
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:07,200
Are you getting used to living upstairs?

80
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:08,950
Yes, I am.

81
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,510
It's not bad.

82
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,560
It's time to eat.

83
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:18,920
Shuyuan.

84
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:21,080
Shuyuan, is the food ready?

85
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,110
Li Shuyuan!

86
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,910
Is the food ready?

87
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,940
I'm not deaf!

88
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,660
Don't shout.

89
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:34,710
This

90
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,919
is all the Zhang family has left.

91
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:39,230
I roughly counted them just now.

92
00:08:39,539 --> 00:08:41,130
There're about 204 gains here

93
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:42,559
or about 198 grains.

94
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:43,720
Let me count for you.

95
00:08:44,059 --> 00:08:45,610
Who are you embarrassing?

96
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,140
Who counts rice at home for fun?

97
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:48,900
What do you mean by embarrassing?

98
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:50,150
We four people need to eat.

99
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,650
I have to divide the food evenly.

100
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:52,510
Tell me,

101
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:53,320
with so little rice,

102
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,520
how should we cook it?

103
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:56,210
Should we steam it, boil it,

104
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:57,370
braise it or fry it?

105
00:08:58,130 --> 00:09:00,780
Dragon meat from heaven is good.

106
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:02,790
But are you capable

107
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:04,120
of getting it?

108
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,720
Sister-in-law, stop.

109
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:09,710
Running away from problems

110
00:09:09,710 --> 00:09:11,720
is not your style, Sister-in-law.

111
00:09:12,210 --> 00:09:14,660
You always take whatever measures necessary

112
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:15,920
to deal with problems.

113
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,180
Right now, the Zhang family

114
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:19,950
has problems

115
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,210
getting enough rice to eat.

116
00:09:21,210 --> 00:09:22,870
Let's talk about it together.

117
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:32,840
Yunqi.

118
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:34,710
You sit down too.

119
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:37,900
L-L-Let me tend the fire first.

120
00:09:44,590 --> 00:09:46,800
Shuyuan, since I came,

121
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:48,830
we haven't really had a good chat.

122
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:49,820
I feel that,

123
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:52,050
no matter what, we are a family.

124
00:09:52,170 --> 00:09:53,930
If there are any difficulties,

125
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,170
we should face them

126
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,260
and discuss openly

127
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:59,230
to figure out a solution together.

128
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:00,470
Now that

129
00:10:00,490 --> 00:10:02,350
I've moved onto the second floor.

130
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:03,900
Miss Liu

131
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,200
has moved out anyway,

132
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:06,890
so let's not talk about her for now.

133
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:08,040
I

134
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:10,730
returned to Shanghai to look for Yunkui.

135
00:10:11,690 --> 00:10:12,660
Right now,

136
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:15,320
I haven't found a way to locate Yunkui,

137
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,110
and Great-grandfather hasn't come back.

138
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:18,850
I asked Yunqi to look for Great-grandfather,

139
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:20,250
but there's no news yet.

140
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,080
I'm genuinely anxious.

141
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:24,090
If anything I've said or done

142
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:25,600
has made you unhappy,

143
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:26,800
I apologize to you

144
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,200
and Yunqi.

145
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:30,130
Please don't take it to heart.

146
00:10:30,150 --> 00:10:31,080
Sister-in-law.

147
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:33,590
This isn't about apologizing or not.

148
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,340
We need to solve

149
00:10:35,370 --> 00:10:37,500
the problem of not having enough to eat.

150
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,190
Yes.

151
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:42,420
Stop pretending to tend the fire.

152
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,660
I'm not pretending.

153
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:44,670
Miss Liu

154
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:46,100
has nothing to do with us.

155
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:48,470
But the man behind her is Manager Hu.

156
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,050
I know his ways

157
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,950
much better than you do.

158
00:10:52,170 --> 00:10:53,150
Zhang Yunqi.

159
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,340
Listen carefully.

160
00:10:54,370 --> 00:10:55,410
You offended Hu.

161
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:56,740
Keep this in mind,

162
00:10:56,770 --> 00:10:58,070
you are in constant danger now.

163
00:10:58,070 --> 00:10:58,950
Sit down!

164
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:02,890
Straighten your back,

165
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:04,190
and act like a man.

166
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:08,090
I have to say this.

167
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:10,780
The problem is
that we can barely make ends meet.

168
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:13,300
Even the best cook
can't cook without any ingredients.

169
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,610
So I'm thinking

170
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:16,700
about asking you to give us some advice

171
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:17,820
on how to solve the problem.

172
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:19,200
Let's think of what we can possibly do.

173
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,470
What are you talking about?

174
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:22,020
Asking Sister-in-law for advice?

175
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:24,680
You're making insinuations and being so harsh.

176
00:11:29,610 --> 00:11:31,850
Sister-in-law, I'm sorry.

177
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,920
Shuyuan spoke rudely.

178
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,610
Her words are harsh yet make sense.

179
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:39,860
If I really lose that job,

180
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,200
we in the future

181
00:11:41,230 --> 00:11:42,870
will definitely have a hard life.

182
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,790
You're quite right, Yunqi.

183
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,860
We are a family.

184
00:11:47,010 --> 00:11:48,290
I know you've been working hard,

185
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,890
and I'm very thankful to you.

186
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:51,540
But you have

187
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:53,680
so many tenants,

188
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,830
including Miss Liu who just moved out.

189
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,760
Shouldn't the rent you collect

190
00:11:57,850 --> 00:12:00,040
be enough to feed us four?

191
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,150
-Well, the rent collected...
-So,

192
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:05,480
Sister-in-law, you don't know the cost of living
because you're not the mistress of the house.

193
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:08,410
The rent is far from enough
to cover the living expense.

194
00:12:08,410 --> 00:12:09,320
The Taku vegetables

195
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,380
we ate the other day

196
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:12,800
-are more and more expensive...
-Why are you talking about Taku vegetables again?

197
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,050
Why are you beating around the bush?

198
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,880
Sister-in-law just said

199
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:17,600
we shouldn't insinuate.

200
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,030
Aren't we talking about rice?

201
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,910
Is there anything valuable left in the house?

202
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:22,330
Of course not.

203
00:12:22,350 --> 00:12:24,140
I've already pawned my dowry from my parents.

204
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:24,540
Well...

205
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:26,660
What about the bracelet Sister-in-law gave you?

206
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:28,880
Don't even mention that bracelet.

207
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,550
I had an expert look at it,

208
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:31,890
and it's not worth much at all.

209
00:12:31,890 --> 00:12:32,920
They said

210
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:34,270
it's some sort of

211
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:35,540
local knockoff.

212
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,360
A local knockoff?

213
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,750
It's not Hotan jade?

214
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,660
It is Hotan jade!

215
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:40,750
It is Hotan jade.

216
00:12:40,770 --> 00:12:41,770
When I got married,

217
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,000
my family gave it to me as a dowry.

218
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,180
How could it not be Hotan jade?

219
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,270
How could her dowry be fake?

220
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:48,380
It's not important whether it's Hotan jade or not.

221
00:12:48,380 --> 00:12:50,320
Hotan jade has different grades.

222
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,420
These things of mine,

223
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:52,480
if they weren't fake,

224
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,620
would have been pawned long ago.

225
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:55,410
Those things are just for show.

226
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,140
Right now, I only have one word to say.

227
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:58,290
That is hate.

228
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:01,690
Look at me. I'm a perfectly capable person.

229
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:03,910
But my hands shake when I hold a needle.

230
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:04,880
When I try to thread a needle,

231
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:06,430
my eyes can't focus.

232
00:13:06,450 --> 00:13:07,980
If only my body were a bit better,

233
00:13:07,980 --> 00:13:09,170
and my eyesight a bit sharper,

234
00:13:09,170 --> 00:13:11,230
I would do a job like mending clothes,

235
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:12,590
or do servant's work for money

236
00:13:12,590 --> 00:13:13,970
to help out with the family expenses.

237
00:13:13,970 --> 00:13:15,440
That way, our life would be better.

238
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:18,370
Then I wouldn't wander around the house all day

239
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:19,670
and being an eyesore.

240
00:13:19,780 --> 00:13:21,470
Then I'll go find a job, okay?

241
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:22,790
I'll look for one tomorrow.

242
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:23,900
If I can't find a long-term job,

243
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,330
I'll do odd jobs to help with expenses.

244
00:13:25,330 --> 00:13:26,340
Is that okay?

245
00:13:26,370 --> 00:13:27,090
No.

246
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:28,440
If you go out to work,

247
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:30,130
who will take care of the baby?

248
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:38,670
Sister-in-law, what you said

249
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,910
is spot on.

250
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:44,700
You are from a wealthy family, Sister-in-law.

251
00:13:44,930 --> 00:13:46,930
You're well-educated and sensible.

252
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,230
What you said

253
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:50,890
shows you're not a naive person.

254
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:54,260
There's a popular saying out there

255
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:58,480
that one who does not work
shouldn't be given food to eat

256
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:01,010
and the laborers are the most honourable.

257
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:04,400
Reaching this consensus today

258
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:06,740
means this chat isn't meaningless.

259
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:08,550
Look at me.

260
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,660
I don't work,

261
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,650
so whenever it rains outside,

262
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:14,090
my back starts hurting.

263
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,080
Yunqi, hurry up.

264
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:18,260
Go back inside and rub it for me.

265
00:14:18,670 --> 00:14:20,470
The rice hasn't been washed yet.

266
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,900
How are we supposed to eat with so little rice?

267
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,080
One who does not work
shouldn't be given food to eat.

268
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,280
We stay hungry today.

269
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:29,200
Don't try to snatch food from Sister-in-law.

270
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:30,410
Hurry up.

271
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:32,540
Baliao points and Dazhui points.

272
00:15:05,590 --> 00:15:07,160
It is pretty cold in here.

273
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:10,160
I'll stoke the stove to make it warmer.

274
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,340
Yunqi.

275
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,040
Do you know how heavy

276
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:25,780
over 200 grains of rice are?

277
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:28,440
I don't know.

278
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:33,380
Just one mace.

279
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:35,710
One mace?

280
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:38,750
There are at least two taels in this bowl.

281
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,960
About 3,000 to 4,000 grains of rice.

282
00:15:41,330 --> 00:15:42,860
Enough to make three or four

283
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,430
bowls of congee.

284
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,120
Shuyuan.

285
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:49,950
I'm going to make congee.

286
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:52,130
Though there's very little rice,

287
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,680
each of us will get a share one deserves.

288
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:57,040
I'll call you when it's ready.

289
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:28,110
[Juren Lane]

290
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,600
Newspaper!

291
00:16:29,970 --> 00:16:33,590
[Barber Shop]

292
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:33,070
The latest issue!

293
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:35,760
Newspapers! Newspapers!

294
00:16:35,810 --> 00:16:37,460
Sir, buy a newspaper?

295
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,900
Sir, would you like a newspaper?

296
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:44,260
[Juren Lane]

297
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:41,690
Newspapers! Newspapers!

298
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:44,720
The latest issue!

299
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:16,000
Sister-in-law.

300
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,130
Washing clothes in such cold weather?

301
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:20,580
Perfect.

302
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,240
After you finish washing these,

303
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,020
could you conveniently

304
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:23,970
take my two pieces

305
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:25,450
and rinse them in the used water?

306
00:18:25,450 --> 00:18:26,930
If I weren't in a hurry to cook,

307
00:18:26,930 --> 00:18:28,020
I would wash them myself.

308
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:30,290
This basin is full of the baby's diapers.

309
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,540
It's been cold the last few days,

310
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:33,610
and the baby had diarrhea.

311
00:18:33,610 --> 00:18:34,840
He even had it this morning.

312
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:35,840
Had loose bowels.

313
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,980
What's the big deal?

314
00:18:38,290 --> 00:18:39,550
I heard

315
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:41,820
some people specifically like to drink children's urine.

316
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:42,620
It's fine.

317
00:18:42,870 --> 00:18:44,550
Don't rush, take your time.

318
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,040
Thanks, Sister-in-law.

319
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:50,110
Mother, look.

320
00:18:50,220 --> 00:18:50,910
Beef.

321
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:51,610
And this.

322
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,380
-Look.
-I got two bottles of perfume today.

323
00:18:53,380 --> 00:18:53,970
Really?

324
00:18:53,990 --> 00:18:55,070
Looks like good stuff to me.

325
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,510
Good heavens.

326
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:58,550
I finally see you today,

327
00:18:58,570 --> 00:18:59,860
and everyone's here.

328
00:18:59,910 --> 00:19:00,650
So what about it?

329
00:19:00,650 --> 00:19:03,110
I told you about the rent increase last time.

330
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:06,280
The war has only been going on for a few months,

331
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:07,590
and you've raised the rent

332
00:19:07,590 --> 00:19:09,440
by five or ten dollars several times.

333
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,260
For a two-month lease,

334
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:12,260
you charge a three-month deposit.

335
00:19:12,540 --> 00:19:14,460
Aren't you taking advantage of the situation

336
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:15,970
and profiteering from the national crisis?

337
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:18,430
Renting out a house makes me a war profiteer?

338
00:19:18,530 --> 00:19:20,880
Then what about you smugglers

339
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:22,910
hoarding and cornering the market?

340
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,860
Instead of talking nonsense,

341
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:27,220
why not have your Yuan make a few more runs?

342
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:28,610
If so, the houses in the whole lane

343
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:30,060
could be bought by you guys,

344
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:31,370
let alone the rent.

345
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:31,800
You!

346
00:19:31,820 --> 00:19:33,570
Dying on the streets costs nothing.

347
00:19:33,570 --> 00:19:34,630
Why don't you do it?

348
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,160
You dare say it again?

349
00:19:36,330 --> 00:19:37,130
Yunqi.

350
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:39,120
-I've had enough of you!
-Yuan.

351
00:19:39,170 --> 00:19:40,400
Stay out of this.

352
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:41,210
Go upstairs.

353
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:42,610
My girl, go upstairs with your brother.

354
00:19:42,610 --> 00:19:44,210
Hurry.

355
00:19:45,170 --> 00:19:46,250
Fine, fine.

356
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,390
Missy.

357
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:49,130
I'll give you the money.

358
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,160
Don't snatch!

359
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:58,860
Here.

360
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:02,180
How dare he yell at me at such a young age?

361
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,930
If it's about who is louder,

362
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:05,570
I can be your grandmother.

363
00:20:12,330 --> 00:20:17,850
Who doesn't want to want to climb higher and higher?

364
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:23,480
Who doesn't wants to make money?

365
00:20:23,970 --> 00:20:28,270
-Although you're before God of Wealth...
-Stop singing.

366
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:43,280
Mrs. Landlady,

367
00:20:43,370 --> 00:20:44,720
having this house,

368
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,000
is almost driving us tenants

369
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,590
to despair.

370
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:50,000
How can she be so cruel?

371
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:50,770
Hey.

372
00:20:50,980 --> 00:20:52,060
There is hot water on the stove.

373
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:53,260
Why didn't you use it?

374
00:20:53,730 --> 00:20:55,210
You haven't finished your confinement month yet.

375
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:56,740
You can't touch cold water,

376
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:57,940
or you'll get sick.

377
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:58,870
Come.

378
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:06,460
Thank you, Auntie Jing.

379
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:07,610
Actually,

380
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,560
you shouldn't even be doing the laundry.

381
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,690
I'll put this on the stove for you.

382
00:21:11,710 --> 00:21:13,170
Remember to use hot water.

383
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:00,180
Zhang Yunqi.

384
00:22:00,670 --> 00:22:01,840
Listen.

385
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,750
I've done all the things

386
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,750
a man should do in this house for you.

387
00:22:06,750 --> 00:22:08,260
What's the use of having you around?

388
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,930
What do you mean by
what's the use of having me around?

389
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:12,130
I'm busy worrying about state affairs.

390
00:22:12,980 --> 00:22:14,500
How is it going?

391
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:18,220
Come look at this.

392
00:22:20,330 --> 00:22:22,890
800 Japanese soldiers died in battle,

393
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:25,090
[Japanese Army didn't escape danger. The Yellow River bridge completed successfully.]

394
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,550
and 4,000 wounded.

395
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:25,570
The enemies...

396
00:22:27,130 --> 00:22:28,410
You're the enemy.

397
00:22:29,270 --> 00:22:34,180
The Chinese Army left 84,000 corpses.

398
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,920
10,500 of their troops were captured.

399
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:40,800
The main spoils include

400
00:22:40,820 --> 00:22:43,290
120,900 rifles,

401
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:45,420
[Japanese Army didn't escape danger. The Yellow River bridge completed successfully.]

402
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:47,240
3,200 heavy and light machine guns,

403
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:48,480
and mortars, and mountain guns...

404
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,590
Okay.

405
00:22:49,610 --> 00:22:50,530
Stop.

406
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,830
This is New Shun Pao,

407
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,840
a newspaper run by the Japanese.

408
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:58,520
Of course it's all about bad news about us.

409
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:00,860
Isn't it about those government bonds
you mentioned before?

410
00:23:00,860 --> 00:23:02,850
We just give them up
in the worst case scenario.

411
00:23:02,850 --> 00:23:04,410
No.

412
00:23:04,530 --> 00:23:08,060
Why is the Chinese Army so disappointing?

413
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:11,880
You made a promise of sure victory
in the war of resistance.

414
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,110
With my country like this,

415
00:23:13,110 --> 00:23:15,840
how am I supposed to live?

416
00:23:16,090 --> 00:23:17,820
Zhang Yunqi.

417
00:23:18,050 --> 00:23:20,060
I've been married to you for so many years,

418
00:23:20,060 --> 00:23:22,540
and I didn't know you were so patriotic.

419
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:25,440
I know exactly what you're up to.

420
00:23:25,550 --> 00:23:27,790
You must be hiding something from me.

421
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:30,150
Confess now,

422
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:32,590
and you'll suffer less.

423
00:23:37,890 --> 00:23:39,070
I'll confess.

424
00:23:40,030 --> 00:23:41,480
But you can't hit me.

425
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:42,650
I won't.

426
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,310
I borrowed money from a loan shark.

427
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:48,570
You did?

428
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,010
The government bonds I bought

429
00:23:50,010 --> 00:23:51,610
were all paid with the money
from the loan shark.

430
00:23:51,610 --> 00:23:52,440
You!

431
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:57,190
You used the money from the loan shark
to buy government bonds?

432
00:23:57,190 --> 00:23:58,430
I won't hit you.

433
00:23:58,450 --> 00:23:59,370
But I'll bite you to death.

434
00:23:59,370 --> 00:23:59,970
Come on.

435
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,060
Since the Sino-Japanese War broke out,

436
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:02,420
they've been dumping them at a 90% discount,

437
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:03,630
so I bought them at the bottom.

438
00:24:03,630 --> 00:24:04,360
They dump,

439
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:05,290
and I buy.

440
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,900
I just want to make some money.

441
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:07,210
Well,

442
00:24:07,210 --> 00:24:07,670
I can't just

443
00:24:07,670 --> 00:24:09,050
let those loan sharks like Hei San

444
00:24:09,050 --> 00:24:10,730
cut off my arms and legs.

445
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:11,960
You deserve it if they

446
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:13,440
cut off your arms and legs.

447
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,110
Well,

448
00:24:14,110 --> 00:24:16,110
I just want to buy my own house.

449
00:24:16,110 --> 00:24:17,170
I'm not wrong, am I?

450
00:24:17,180 --> 00:24:18,070
House?

451
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,190
I want to have my own son.

452
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:21,720
A son?

453
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:23,050
Then I can be dignified.

454
00:24:23,050 --> 00:24:24,690
But now the interest is snowballing.

455
00:24:24,690 --> 00:24:25,930
What should I do?

456
00:24:26,050 --> 00:24:27,000
Zhang Yunqi.

457
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,670
You've lost your mind.

458
00:24:28,790 --> 00:24:30,590
Don't you know the interest rate
set by loan sharks

459
00:24:30,590 --> 00:24:32,610
is many times higher
than that of government bonds?

460
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:33,400
Great.

461
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:34,410
Now you offended

462
00:24:34,430 --> 00:24:35,990
Manager Hu at work.

463
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:37,550
And you can't pay back the money.

464
00:24:37,550 --> 00:24:38,620
It's like your brain is full of

465
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:40,240
Japanese soapy water.

466
00:24:40,260 --> 00:24:41,440
Just wait for death.

467
00:24:41,460 --> 00:24:42,790
I've talked to Manager Hu.

468
00:24:42,790 --> 00:24:44,110
He said there was way for me to make up.

469
00:24:44,110 --> 00:24:44,820
Get out first.

470
00:24:44,820 --> 00:24:45,380
No.

471
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:46,580
Zhang Yunqi.

472
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:48,620
I'm trying to solve the problem for you.

473
00:24:48,620 --> 00:24:49,830
Stop being

474
00:24:49,860 --> 00:24:51,070
a coward.

475
00:24:51,330 --> 00:24:52,460
You think I'm too tall and strong

476
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:53,880
to get in there, right?

477
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,240
Don't cross the line.

478
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,870
Otherwise, I'll turn over the bed.

479
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:57,540
I'll count to three.

480
00:24:57,540 --> 00:24:58,490
Get out.

481
00:24:58,760 --> 00:24:59,320
Three.

482
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:01,320
Then you can't hit me.

483
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:03,260
I won't.

484
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,480
And you can't bite me.

485
00:25:04,570 --> 00:25:05,610
I won't.

486
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:12,700
Get out.

487
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:25,030
Speak.

488
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:26,910
What did Manager Hu ask you to do?

489
00:25:27,410 --> 00:25:29,010
Do you remember Fujita?

490
00:25:29,390 --> 00:25:30,110
Who?

491
00:25:31,830 --> 00:25:32,910
The one

492
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,830
who often appears in Hongkou.

493
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:37,270
Some Japanese cultural businessman.

494
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:38,870
You said you wouldn't hit me.

495
00:25:38,940 --> 00:25:40,640
You are so bold.

496
00:25:40,670 --> 00:25:43,150
You want to follow Manager Hu
and cozy up to those Japanese?

497
00:25:43,150 --> 00:25:45,440
It's no use hitting me.

498
00:25:48,490 --> 00:25:50,360
Listen to me.

499
00:25:52,370 --> 00:25:53,550
Manager Hu

500
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:56,060
said when the war broke out

501
00:25:56,610 --> 00:25:58,130
that if China couldn't win,

502
00:25:58,130 --> 00:26:00,360
he would do business with the Japanese

503
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:01,490
in secret.

504
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:04,340
He said Fujita wanted to settle down in Shanghai

505
00:26:04,340 --> 00:26:06,000
and was interested in buying our house.

506
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:06,800
I said, "Bah,

507
00:26:06,820 --> 00:26:08,090
you traitor!"

508
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:10,340
But Manager Hu said

509
00:26:10,370 --> 00:26:12,090
if we can help him get this done,

510
00:26:12,090 --> 00:26:13,330
I'll be able to pay off

511
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:14,650
all my debts.

512
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:17,290
And he can even take me in on some business.

513
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:20,510
I was thinking maybe I should
just pretend to agree,

514
00:26:20,530 --> 00:26:22,550
make some quick money with them,

515
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:25,100
and solve our urgent crisis.

516
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,530
Interacting with the Japanese

517
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:29,910
might give you another way out.

518
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:32,100
The problem is, do you know

519
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,790
that those jerks

520
00:26:34,090 --> 00:26:36,370
are completely inhuman when they act up?

521
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:38,200
Working for them

522
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:39,670
is like having got a snot.

523
00:26:39,690 --> 00:26:41,850
Once you work for them,
you won't get rid of them.

524
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:43,120
One word for you.

525
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:44,090
Traitor.

526
00:26:44,790 --> 00:26:45,960
Who's a traitor?

527
00:26:45,990 --> 00:26:47,120
I am not a traitor.

528
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,070
Even in the worst-case scenario,

529
00:26:49,070 --> 00:26:51,470
even if our troops fight their way back now,

530
00:26:51,530 --> 00:26:53,650
we are still much better

531
00:26:53,670 --> 00:26:55,220
than those who do lip-service patriotism, right?

532
00:26:55,220 --> 00:26:57,050
We show our patriotism with real money.

533
00:26:57,050 --> 00:26:59,180
When it comes to practicing patriotism,
who can beat us?

534
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:00,200
Our Zhang family

535
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,800
is full of loyal martyrs.

536
00:27:02,210 --> 00:27:03,020
Full of...

537
00:27:04,110 --> 00:27:05,620
Full of patriots.

538
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,640
So,

539
00:27:07,330 --> 00:27:09,200
I think we should

540
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:12,770
secretly get along with the Japanese

541
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:15,360
and make friends with them.

542
00:27:15,380 --> 00:27:17,920
They might save us at a critical moment.

543
00:27:17,950 --> 00:27:18,880
It's better than

544
00:27:18,930 --> 00:27:20,090
watching Hei San cutting off

545
00:27:20,090 --> 00:27:22,020
my arms and legs and doing nothing.

546
00:27:22,630 --> 00:27:23,880
This is a bad idea.

547
00:27:24,230 --> 00:27:25,630
The worst possible idea.

548
00:27:26,230 --> 00:27:28,070
It's a move of desperation.

549
00:27:28,260 --> 00:27:29,500
The Japanese want this house.

550
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:30,930
I also want it.

551
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:35,030
Anyway, when you are with them,

552
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:36,920
you have to be very, very careful.

553
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:38,950
So now,

554
00:27:39,870 --> 00:27:42,130
we can only use some money
to pave the way.

555
00:27:42,780 --> 00:27:44,170
Do you have any on hand?

556
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:52,000
Give me a bit more.

557
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:52,680
Get out.

558
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,450
You are so useless.

559
00:28:03,610 --> 00:28:05,110
Tell me.

560
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,770
How did I end up marrying someone like you?

561
00:28:10,210 --> 00:28:14,200
That's because you are a very understanding wife.

562
00:28:18,270 --> 00:28:19,250
Zuliang.

563
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:23,440
[Wuhan]

564
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:23,430
You've been asleep for seven whole days.

565
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:27,020
You either had a fever
or were talking in your sleep.

566
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:30,120
I was so worried.

567
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:32,510
I experienced everything.

568
00:28:33,940 --> 00:28:34,790
I witnessed

569
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:36,550
one sacrifice

570
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:38,210
after

571
00:28:39,290 --> 00:28:40,810
another.

572
00:28:42,010 --> 00:28:45,070
We were full of high spirit
when we went to join the army.

573
00:28:45,340 --> 00:28:47,140
In just a few short months,

574
00:28:47,650 --> 00:28:49,910
of all of us who joined the army together,

575
00:28:50,150 --> 00:28:51,750
I'm the only one still alive.

576
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:53,310
Sun

577
00:28:54,430 --> 00:28:56,850
had the highest military rank among us.

578
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,950
The day Nanjing City fell,

579
00:29:00,930 --> 00:29:02,730
he took 70 or 80 wounded soldiers

580
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:04,720
from the field hospital

581
00:29:05,430 --> 00:29:07,750
to retreat toward the Xiaguan shore.

582
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:11,620
But there wasn't a single boat on the shore to cross the river.

583
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,290
The Japanese 45th Infantry Regiment

584
00:29:13,290 --> 00:29:14,820
came at and flanked them.

585
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,590
One of our wounded said,

586
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,130
"Sir,

587
00:29:18,740 --> 00:29:20,620
you have the highest rank among us.

588
00:29:20,620 --> 00:29:22,050
You should take command."

589
00:29:22,050 --> 00:29:24,180
Sun knew little about military strategies.

590
00:29:24,180 --> 00:29:25,660
He just said one thing,

591
00:29:25,950 --> 00:29:27,040
"Brothers,

592
00:29:27,300 --> 00:29:28,850
fight the Japanese."

593
00:29:29,590 --> 00:29:31,790
According to the Japanese battle reports,

594
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:34,330
the Chinese kept swarming over.

595
00:29:34,980 --> 00:29:37,550
They did nothing but fought to the death,

596
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,000
over and over again,

597
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:42,610
flesh and blood flying everywhere,
everyone covered in blood.

598
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:45,180
Guang was sent
to the No.3 Department of the hospital.

599
00:29:45,180 --> 00:29:46,170
When retreating,

600
00:29:46,170 --> 00:29:48,480
the No.3 Department
had no means of transportation.

601
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,480
They had no idea where to retreat to.

602
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:52,300
The Japanese Army rushed in

603
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:53,670
and carried out

604
00:29:53,970 --> 00:29:55,120
an indiscriminate massacre

605
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,320
against the doctors,

606
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,920
nurses, and wounded soldiers.

607
00:29:59,670 --> 00:30:00,720
They didn't even

608
00:30:00,740 --> 00:30:01,940
use guns and bullets.

609
00:30:02,220 --> 00:30:04,590
Instead, they fought directly with bayonets.

610
00:30:04,590 --> 00:30:07,310
Guang rushed up to negotiate with the Japanese.

611
00:30:08,190 --> 00:30:09,600
Before he

612
00:30:09,940 --> 00:30:11,380
could say anything,

613
00:30:12,020 --> 00:30:14,790
he was pierced through by a Japanese bayonet.

614
00:30:16,260 --> 00:30:17,800
When he died,

615
00:30:18,630 --> 00:30:20,840
he was still holding an IV bottle.

616
00:30:21,290 --> 00:30:22,530
I heard this

617
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,040
from a doctor friend

618
00:30:24,040 --> 00:30:25,880
who managed to escape.

619
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:29,830
Shen and I were both sent to the general hospital.

620
00:30:29,940 --> 00:30:31,870
When we retreated to Yijiang Gate,

621
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,330
we were trampled by retreating soldiers.

622
00:30:34,530 --> 00:30:35,370
Shen, to protect

623
00:30:35,370 --> 00:30:36,900
the 20 or 30 wounded soldiers behind him,

624
00:30:36,900 --> 00:30:37,690
shouted,

625
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:39,770
"Brothers!

626
00:30:39,790 --> 00:30:43,260
Behind us are wounded brothers!

627
00:30:43,410 --> 00:30:45,300
Don't touch them!"

628
00:30:46,350 --> 00:30:48,110
But who would listen?

629
00:30:49,110 --> 00:30:50,770
The retreating soldiers

630
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,830
surged over them like a tide.

631
00:30:53,150 --> 00:30:55,040
Shen shouted at me,

632
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,830
but I couldn't hear him at all.

633
00:30:57,230 --> 00:30:58,670
After the retreating soldiers dispersed,

634
00:30:58,670 --> 00:30:59,530
I ran over

635
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:00,720
and picked Shen up.

636
00:31:01,390 --> 00:31:03,230
Shen was trampled

637
00:31:03,770 --> 00:31:05,630
that he was barely recognizable.

638
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:07,640
Even now,

639
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,360
I just want to know

640
00:31:10,090 --> 00:31:13,480
what Shen was trying to say to me.

641
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:17,120
I'm not afraid of sacrifice,

642
00:31:17,350 --> 00:31:18,630
but I can't accept

643
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:20,170
meaningless sacrifices.

644
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:22,130
What do you think is meaningful?

645
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:24,090
To die a glorious death in battle,

646
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:26,430
to sacrifice for the country, to die a worthy death.

647
00:31:26,430 --> 00:31:27,800
But so many sacrifices

648
00:31:27,830 --> 00:31:29,300
were due to absurd commands.

649
00:31:29,300 --> 00:31:31,340
In Nanjing, because the commanders left without a word,

650
00:31:31,340 --> 00:31:33,000
the defeated army scattered,

651
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:35,200
and the retreat turned into a stampede.

652
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,460
So many of our brothers

653
00:31:36,570 --> 00:31:37,530
lost their lives

654
00:31:37,550 --> 00:31:39,040
because of their superiors' mistakes.

655
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:39,900
The Suzhou–Fushan Line

656
00:31:39,900 --> 00:31:40,880
and the Wuxi–Jiangyin Line

657
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:42,840
were claimed to be the Maginot Line of the East.

658
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:43,590
But the so-called

659
00:31:43,590 --> 00:31:44,960
permanent reinforced concrete

660
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:47,030
was only cement on the outside.

661
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:48,270
It collapsed after a hit from a single artillery shell.

662
00:31:48,270 --> 00:31:49,910
Inside were rotten bamboos.

663
00:31:49,940 --> 00:31:51,440
Besides corruption,

664
00:31:51,460 --> 00:31:52,490
there was incompetence

665
00:31:52,490 --> 00:31:53,510
and selfishness.

666
00:31:54,350 --> 00:31:56,570
Even in the face of national crisis,

667
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:57,790
those upper-class figures

668
00:31:57,790 --> 00:31:59,770
still couldn't change their ways.

669
00:32:00,270 --> 00:32:01,110
Zuliang,

670
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,340
has your confidence

671
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:04,270
wavered?

672
00:32:04,330 --> 00:32:05,440
I don't know.

673
00:32:05,870 --> 00:32:07,240
I've witnessed too many things

674
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,440
that make me reflect.

675
00:32:08,590 --> 00:32:11,160
Can our patriotic passion
and willingess to sacrifice our lives

676
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,400
really save our country?

677
00:32:13,590 --> 00:32:16,070
What on earth did we do wrong?

678
00:32:17,510 --> 00:32:19,240
Your Ladyship, Young Master Luo.

679
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,070
Xiaoyue.

680
00:32:20,310 --> 00:32:21,310
Young Master Luo.

681
00:32:21,830 --> 00:32:23,050
I just want to ask,

682
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,790
during the Battle of Shanghai,

683
00:32:24,790 --> 00:32:25,510
when you were in the hospital,

684
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:28,040
did you see any wounded from the 87th Brigade?

685
00:32:28,540 --> 00:32:30,540
The 87th Brigade? Who are you asking about?

686
00:32:30,540 --> 00:32:31,650
Wanfu.

687
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:35,810
Meng Wanfu joined the army the day
before we got married.

688
00:32:35,810 --> 00:32:37,270
He was in the 87th Brigade.

689
00:32:37,410 --> 00:32:38,810
The brigade commander is

690
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:40,110
Zhang Yunkui.

691
00:32:41,770 --> 00:32:44,340
D-D-Do you know anything about them?

692
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:45,430
Xiaoyue,

693
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:46,770
I heard that

694
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,770
the entire 87th Brigade sacrificed for the country.

695
00:32:49,770 --> 00:32:51,010
What do you mean by

696
00:32:52,830 --> 00:32:54,430
sacrificed for the country?

697
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:55,470
It means

698
00:32:58,090 --> 00:32:59,420
they all died in battle.

699
00:33:09,710 --> 00:33:18,900
[Meng Wanfu of the 87th Brigade]

700
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,810
Xiaoyue,

701
00:33:42,470 --> 00:33:43,940
cry if you want to.

702
00:33:44,750 --> 00:33:45,750
Don't hold it in.

703
00:33:47,650 --> 00:33:48,610
Your Ladyship.

704
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,650
I won't cry.

705
00:33:53,350 --> 00:33:55,230
I'm not able to cry anymore.

706
00:33:58,030 --> 00:34:02,790
-I knew it.
-The peoples of China are at their most critical time.

707
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:06,640
-Everybody must roar defiance.
-Xiaoyue.

708
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:10,510
Arise! Arise! Arise!‌‌‌‌

709
00:34:10,510 --> 00:34:12,630
Millions of hearts with one mind,

710
00:34:12,630 --> 00:34:14,800
Brave the enemy's gunfire

711
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:15,840
March On!

712
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:18,100
Brave the enemy's gunfire

713
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:22,400
March on! March on and on!‌‌‌‌

714
00:34:22,670 --> 00:34:26,190
-Arise, we who refuse to be slaves!
-Uncle, this leaflet...

715
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:31,550
-Take a look at it.
-With our very flesh and blood, let us build our new Great Wall!

716
00:34:31,590 --> 00:34:36,550
The peoples of China are at their most critical time.

717
00:34:36,550 --> 00:34:40,760
-Sir, please take a look at this leaflet.
-Everybody must roar defiance.

718
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:43,920
-Miss.
-Arise! Arise! Arise!‌‌‌‌

719
00:34:44,190 --> 00:34:46,210
Millions of hearts with one mind.

720
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,360
Brave the enemy's gunfire.

721
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:49,320
March On!

722
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:51,550
Brave the enemy's gunfire.

723
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:55,710
March on! March on and on!‌‌‌‌

724
00:34:56,590 --> 00:34:59,620
Arise, we who refuse to be slaves!

725
00:34:59,650 --> 00:35:04,730
With our very flesh and blood, let us build our new Great Wall!

726
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:10,230
The peoples of China are at their most critical time.

727
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:14,190
Everybody must roar defiance.

728
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,570
It's the Communist Party of China.

729
00:35:15,570 --> 00:35:17,330
It's a leaflet from the Eighth Route Army.

730
00:35:17,330 --> 00:35:18,590
The Eighth Route Army,

731
00:35:19,270 --> 00:35:20,830
115th Division

732
00:35:20,850 --> 00:35:22,520
achieved the Victory at Pingxingguan.

733
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:23,320
At that time,

734
00:35:23,340 --> 00:35:25,320
we all went to the streets to celebrate.

735
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,620
It's also said

736
00:35:26,810 --> 00:35:27,670
the Eighth Route Army

737
00:35:27,670 --> 00:35:29,600
is an expert on guerrilla warfare.

738
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:30,970
Mr. Zhou Enlai

739
00:35:30,990 --> 00:35:31,580
is going to give a speech at

740
00:35:31,580 --> 00:35:33,220
Wuhan University next week.

741
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:36,520
[Excerpts from Ten-Point Program for Resistance Against Japan and National Salvation]

742
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:35,060
If you have difficulties,

743
00:35:35,060 --> 00:35:36,990
go to the Eighth Route Army Office.

744
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,110
Brother,

745
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,230
are you going back

746
00:35:51,470 --> 00:35:52,820
to see the brigade commander's wife?

747
00:35:52,820 --> 00:35:54,480
I already have a place to live.

748
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:55,970
Why would I look for her?

749
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:57,730
I'm going to look for Old Master.

750
00:35:57,730 --> 00:35:59,360
Your brigade commander is gone.

751
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,770
Why are you going to look for the Old Master?

752
00:36:00,770 --> 00:36:01,940
Aren't you just trying

753
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,650
to go find the brigade commander's wife?

754
00:36:03,650 --> 00:36:04,940
Stop joking around.

755
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:06,710
Old Master promised

756
00:36:06,730 --> 00:36:09,190
to give me the money I can use
to find Xiaoyue in Wuhan.

757
00:36:09,190 --> 00:36:10,310
If I don't go find him,

758
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:12,040
who else can I ask for the money?

759
00:36:15,390 --> 00:36:16,250
Let me tell you,

760
00:36:16,330 --> 00:36:17,850
watch your mouth

761
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,420
and stop talking nonsense to me.

762
00:36:19,420 --> 00:36:19,950
Brother.

763
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,360
Take me with you.

764
00:36:23,310 --> 00:36:24,320
Ms. Ding.

765
00:36:25,070 --> 00:36:26,930
We've got plenty of hands as it is.

766
00:36:30,580 --> 00:36:31,630
Look.

767
00:36:32,610 --> 00:36:33,250
These are all

768
00:36:33,250 --> 00:36:34,650
people looking for jobs.

769
00:36:35,270 --> 00:36:36,000
Besides,

770
00:36:36,020 --> 00:36:37,420
you have a child with you.

771
00:36:37,740 --> 00:36:39,180
We are not some

772
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,490
charity organization.

773
00:36:40,490 --> 00:36:41,530
Go somewhere else

774
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:42,490
to try your luck.

775
00:36:43,410 --> 00:36:44,220
I understand.

776
00:36:46,450 --> 00:36:47,340
Thank you.

777
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:48,240
Sorry.

778
00:36:54,610 --> 00:36:55,470
Next.

779
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:56,940
Ma'am.

780
00:37:57,980 --> 00:37:58,430
Hello.

781
00:37:58,480 --> 00:37:59,380
Have you seen a child

782
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:00,310
about this tall?

783
00:38:01,170 --> 00:38:01,920
Thank you.

784
00:38:43,460 --> 00:38:44,160
Dad?

785
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:45,680
Dad!

786
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:46,680
Dad!

787
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,370
S-S-Sorry, my mistake.

788
00:38:50,390 --> 00:38:51,420
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

789
00:38:51,420 --> 00:38:52,210
I'm sorry.

790
00:38:52,690 --> 00:38:53,570
I'm sorry.

791
00:39:11,070 --> 00:39:12,150
Newspapers!

792
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:13,630
Newspapers!

793
00:39:14,570 --> 00:39:15,810
Newspapers!

794
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:19,390
Newspapers!

795
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:21,540
Newspapers!

796
00:39:28,590 --> 00:39:30,860
[Ha Tong Law Office]

797
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:40,150
[Ha Tong Law Office]

798
00:39:43,230 --> 00:39:43,880
Hello.

799
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:46,850
Who are you looking for?

800
00:39:47,690 --> 00:39:48,520
Hello.

801
00:39:49,850 --> 00:39:50,690
Is

802
00:39:50,710 --> 00:39:52,460
Lawyer Wu Jianzhang here?

803
00:39:53,890 --> 00:39:55,030
Hiring Lawyer Wu

804
00:39:55,060 --> 00:39:56,440
to handle a lawsuit

805
00:39:56,460 --> 00:39:58,630
costs at least 300 legal tender dollars.

806
00:39:58,630 --> 00:39:59,380
I

807
00:40:00,190 --> 00:40:02,110
want to talk to him first.

808
00:40:02,360 --> 00:40:04,290
My situation is a bit complicated.

809
00:40:04,350 --> 00:40:04,830
Madam.

810
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:05,920
As I just said,

811
00:40:06,170 --> 00:40:07,350
Lawyer Wu charges at least

812
00:40:07,350 --> 00:40:09,170
300 legal tender dollars for a lawsuit.

813
00:40:09,170 --> 00:40:10,800
And there's a reservation fee.

814
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,000
You can register now,

815
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:12,720
or

816
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:14,040
think about it.

817
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,490
I know about Lawyer Wu.

818
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,140
After January 28 Incident,

819
00:40:19,140 --> 00:40:20,150
he sent letters to

820
00:40:20,190 --> 00:40:21,440
lawyers' associations across the country

821
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,880
to aid the 19th Route Army.

822
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,570
After the Battle of Shanghai broke out,

823
00:40:24,570 --> 00:40:25,900
he volunteered to be

824
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,500
the captain of the lawyers' unit of

825
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,870
National Salvation Bond Solicitation Committee,

826
00:40:28,870 --> 00:40:29,930
contributing both money and effort.

827
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:31,710
-I believe...
-I'm sorry, Madam.

828
00:40:31,710 --> 00:40:32,980
What are you trying to say

829
00:40:32,980 --> 00:40:34,500
with all this?

830
00:40:38,510 --> 00:40:39,520
My husband

831
00:40:39,970 --> 00:40:40,850
is the Brigade Commander of the 87th Brigade,

832
00:40:40,850 --> 00:40:42,380
Zhang Yunkui.

833
00:40:42,410 --> 00:40:42,890
Madam.

834
00:40:42,910 --> 00:40:45,710
-You can't do this.
-I'm holding his posthumous child.

835
00:40:45,710 --> 00:40:47,100
-Lawyer Wu
-Madam, you can't do this.

836
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:48,230
-Lawyer Wu.
-Madam.

837
00:40:48,310 --> 00:40:49,370
-Stop.
-Lawyer Wu.

838
00:40:50,230 --> 00:40:51,310
Lawyer Wu.

839
00:40:53,490 --> 00:40:54,100
Madam.

840
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:56,270
You just said

841
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,480
the 87th Brigade.

842
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,510
The 87th Brigade.

843
00:40:59,770 --> 00:41:01,170
Then Zhang Yunkui was...

844
00:41:01,590 --> 00:41:02,960
He was my husband.

845
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:08,100
Nice to meet you, Mrs. Zhang.

846
00:41:08,100 --> 00:41:09,420
I am Wu Jianzhang.

847
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,130
Mrs. Zhang.

848
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:19,240
Please come in.

849
00:41:20,730 --> 00:41:21,590
Thank you.

850
00:41:27,130 --> 00:41:27,480
This way.

851
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:28,460
Mrs. Zhang, please take a seat.

852
00:41:28,460 --> 00:41:29,120
Have a seat.

853
00:41:29,980 --> 00:41:30,640
Have a seat.

854
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:35,690
Speaking of which,

855
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:37,330
I actually have quite a bond

856
00:41:37,330 --> 00:41:38,590
with the 87th Brigade.

857
00:41:38,850 --> 00:41:39,890
I am from Luodian.

858
00:41:40,340 --> 00:41:42,420
My hometown is in Baijiazhai.

859
00:41:43,970 --> 00:41:44,570
Here.

860
00:41:51,940 --> 00:41:53,750
It's only a few miles away

861
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:55,310
from the 87th Brigade's position.

862
00:41:55,310 --> 00:41:56,300
My father told me

863
00:41:56,630 --> 00:41:57,570
that in that battle,

864
00:41:57,570 --> 00:41:58,530
the 87th Brigade

865
00:41:58,630 --> 00:41:59,830
fought very bravely,

866
00:41:59,870 --> 00:42:01,260
and the battle was brutal.

867
00:42:01,260 --> 00:42:02,620
When it rained,

868
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:05,000
the whole street turned red.

869
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:06,410
The position was lost,

870
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:07,760
but

871
00:42:07,980 --> 00:42:09,340
the folks all know

872
00:42:09,620 --> 00:42:10,530
that the 87th Brigade's

873
00:42:10,530 --> 00:42:11,790
thousands of brothers

874
00:42:11,870 --> 00:42:13,410
fought the Japanese with bayonets

875
00:42:13,410 --> 00:42:14,740
until the last man died.

876
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:16,670
They saw it with their own eyes

877
00:42:16,670 --> 00:42:18,270
and engraved it in their hearts.

878
00:42:18,270 --> 00:42:19,770
The newspaper said

879
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:20,860
Brigade Commander Zhang

880
00:42:20,860 --> 00:42:22,570
and his men were deserters.

881
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,400
Those people were

882
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:27,120
spreading rumors, taking advantage of the fact

883
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:29,050
that the dead can't speak for themselves.

884
00:42:29,050 --> 00:42:30,580
I don't believe that rumor.

885
00:42:30,670 --> 00:42:32,070
The folks of Luodian

886
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:34,140
will never believe it either.

887
00:42:34,670 --> 00:42:35,420
Mrs. Zhang,

888
00:42:35,890 --> 00:42:37,360
if you have any difficulties,

889
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,290
just let me know.

890
00:42:38,690 --> 00:42:39,690
If I can help,

891
00:42:40,450 --> 00:42:41,190
I, Wu,

892
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:43,010
will definitely do my best.

893
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:50,480
As a native of Luodian,

894
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:52,240
on behalf of the folks there

895
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,200
to Brigade Commander Zhang,

896
00:42:54,940 --> 00:42:55,910
to you,

897
00:42:56,480 --> 00:42:57,290
and to

898
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:59,780
all the soldiers of the 87th Brigade,

899
00:43:00,230 --> 00:43:01,150
I bow.

900
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:02,430
Thank you.
